<h3 id="table-with-status"><a class="header-anchor" href="#table-with-status" aria-hidden="true">¶</a> Table with status</h3>
<p>You can highlight your table content to distinguish between &quot;success, information, warning, danger&quot; and other states.</p>
<demo-block class="demo-box" :jsfiddle="{&quot;html&quot;:&quot;&lt;template&gt;\n  &lt;el-table :data=\&quot;tableData2\&quot; style=\&quot;width: 100%\&quot; :row-class-name=\&quot;tableRowClassName\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;el-table-column prop=\&quot;date\&quot; label=\&quot;Date\&quot; width=\&quot;180\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;/el-table-column&gt;\n    &lt;el-table-column prop=\&quot;name\&quot; label=\&quot;Name\&quot; width=\&quot;180\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;/el-table-column&gt;\n    &lt;el-table-column prop=\&quot;address\&quot; label=\&quot;Address\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;/el-table-column&gt;\n  &lt;/el-table&gt;\n&lt;/template&gt;\n\n\n\n\n&quot;,&quot;script&quot;:&quot;\n  export default {\n    methods: {\n      tableRowClassName(row, index) {\n        if (index === 1) {\n          return 'info-row';\n        } else if (index === 3) {\n          return 'positive-row';\n        }\n        return '';\n      }\n    },\n    data() {\n      return {\n        tableData2:  [{\n          date: '2016-05-03',\n          name: 'Tom',\n          address: 'No. 189, Grove St, Los Angeles'\n        }, {\n          date: '2016-05-02',\n          name: 'Tom',\n          address: 'No. 189, Grove St, Los Angeles'\n        }, {\n          date: '2016-05-04',\n          name: 'Tom',\n          address: 'No. 189, Grove St, Los Angeles'\n        }, {\n          date: '2016-05-01',\n          name: 'Tom',\n          address: 'No. 189, Grove St, Los Angeles'\n        }]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n&quot;,&quot;style&quot;:&quot;\n  .el-table .info-row {\n    background: #c9e5f5;\n  }\n\n  .el-table .positive-row {\n    background: #e2f0e4;\n  }\n&quot;}">
                    <div class="source" slot="source"><template>
  <el-table :data="tableData2" style="width: 100%" :row-class-name="tableRowClassName">
    <el-table-column prop="date" label="Date" width="180">
    </el-table-column>
    <el-table-column prop="name" label="Name" width="180">
    </el-table-column>
    <el-table-column prop="address" label="Address">
    </el-table-column>
  </el-table>
</template>




</div>
                    <p>Use <code>row-class-name</code> in <code>el-table</code> to add custom classes to a certain row. Then you can style it with custom classes.</p>

