<h3 id="single-select"><a class="header-anchor" href="#single-select" aria-hidden="true">¶</a> Single select</h3>
<p>Single row selection is supported.</p>
<demo-block class="demo-box" :jsfiddle="{&quot;html&quot;:&quot;&lt;template&gt;\n  &lt;el-table ref=\&quot;singleTable\&quot; :data=\&quot;tableData\&quot; highlight-current-row @current-change=\&quot;handleCurrentChange\&quot; style=\&quot;width: 100%\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;el-table-column type=\&quot;index\&quot; width=\&quot;50\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;/el-table-column&gt;\n    &lt;el-table-column property=\&quot;date\&quot; label=\&quot;Date\&quot; width=\&quot;120\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;/el-table-column&gt;\n    &lt;el-table-column property=\&quot;name\&quot; label=\&quot;Name\&quot; width=\&quot;120\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;/el-table-column&gt;\n    &lt;el-table-column property=\&quot;address\&quot; label=\&quot;Address\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;/el-table-column&gt;\n  &lt;/el-table&gt;\n  &lt;div style=\&quot;margin-top: 20px\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;el-button @click=\&quot;setCurrent(tableData[1])\&quot;&gt;Select second row&lt;/el-button&gt;\n    &lt;el-button @click=\&quot;setCurrent()\&quot;&gt;Clear selection&lt;/el-button&gt;\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/template&gt;\n\n\n&quot;,&quot;script&quot;:&quot;\n  export default {\n    data() {\n      return {\n        tableData: [{\n          date: '2016-05-03',\n          name: 'Tom',\n          address: 'No. 189, Grove St, Los Angeles'\n        }, {\n          date: '2016-05-02',\n          name: 'Tom',\n          address: 'No. 189, Grove St, Los Angeles'\n        }, {\n          date: '2016-05-04',\n          name: 'Tom',\n          address: 'No. 189, Grove St, Los Angeles'\n        }, {\n          date: '2016-05-01',\n          name: 'Tom',\n          address: 'No. 189, Grove St, Los Angeles'\n        }],\n        currentRow: null\n      }\n    },\n\n    methods: {\n      setCurrent(row) {\n        this.$refs.singleTable.setCurrentRow(row);\n      },\n      handleCurrentChange(val) {\n        this.currentRow = val;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n&quot;,&quot;style&quot;:null}">
                    <div class="source" slot="source"><template>
  <el-table ref="singleTable" :data="tableData" highlight-current-row="" @current-change="handleCurrentChange" style="width: 100%">
    <el-table-column type="index" width="50">
    </el-table-column>
    <el-table-column property="date" label="Date" width="120">
    </el-table-column>
    <el-table-column property="name" label="Name" width="120">
    </el-table-column>
    <el-table-column property="address" label="Address">
    </el-table-column>
  </el-table>
  <div style="margin-top: 20px">
    <el-button @click="setCurrent(tableData[1])">Select second row</el-button>
    <el-button @click="setCurrent()">Clear selection</el-button>
  </div>
</template>


</div>
                    <p>Table supports single row selection. You can activate it by adding the <code>highlight-current-row</code> attribute. An event called <code>current-change</code> will be triggered when row selection changes, and its parameters are the rows after and before this change: <code>currentRow</code> and <code>oldCurrentRow</code>. If you need to display row index, you can add a new <code>el-table-column</code> with its <code>type</code> attribute assigned to <code>index</code>, and you will see the index starting from 1.</p>

