                    <p>Set attribute <code>sortable</code> in a certain column to sort the data based on this column. It accepts <code>Boolean</code> with a default value <code>false</code>. Set table attribute <code>default-sort</code> to determine default sort column and order. To apply your own sorting rules, use <code>sort-method</code>. If you need remote sorting from backend, set <code>sortable</code> to <code>custom</code>, and listen to the <code>sort-change</code> event on Table. In the event handler, you have access to the sorting column and sorting order so that you can fetch sorted table data from API. In this example we use another attribute named <code>formatter</code> to format the value of certain columns. It accepts a function which has two parameters: <code>row</code> and <code>column</code>. You can handle it according to your own needs.</p>

